RIYADH: Saudi Health Minister Fahad Al-Jalajel met with Francesco Rocca, president of the International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies, and his delegation in Riyadh recently. The meeting discussed international developments and mutual cooperation initiatives, while Rocca voiced his appreciation for the Kingdomâ€™s global humanitarian efforts through the Saudi Crescent Authority. Health Ministry spokesperson Muhammad Al-Abdulali and Vice President of the Saudi Red Crescent Authority Fahd Al-Hajjaj also attended the meeting. Later, the delegation visited Seha Virtual Hospital, which connects patients digitally to a network of 130 hospitals around the Kingdom.